  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An optimal angiographic viewing angle is critical for correct diagnosis and intervention in
      coronary bifurcation lesion percutaneous coronary interventions (PCI). The current study aims
      at validating a dedicated software tool (MEDIS, Leiden, The Netherlands) that will improve
      the selection of the best viewing angle.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
